my merch collab with @madrome is live now 🫧 when I was thinking of what my first merch should be, I really didn’t want to just slap my logo on a shirt. I wanted something that embodies the duality of femininity and the DJ culture. 

Madison and I were sitting one night discussing ideas over a glass of wine, she pulled out a notebook and started sketching. Every design you see was hand drawn, specifically tailored to the diversity of Planet Zuzy & the aesthetic of @madrome. Hope you love them as much as we do 💗

This is very bittersweet to even write, never thought I’d have to say good bye to this city, and the beautiful people I’ve met here, so soon. I owe it all to you, NYC. There’s no other place on this world that would have taken me from DJ’ing a small little bar in LES, to playing over 50 shows, gathering 3 million streams, connecting with 27,000 of you, and meeting the people that make up my team, that I get to call family forever - all in less than 2 years. 

If it were up to me, I wouldn’t leave you. But it’s time for a new chapter, and you can bet your ass that I’ll be back. 

I can’t help but feel like it was somewhat meant to be? My last 2 shows in the city are happening at 2 amazing venues, both with incredible artists I look up to. Links in bio.

Love is Waiting, my second single with @ishan.us is out now. It’s dedicated to this city, and you’ll see it all in the music video (coming soon)

Thank you from the bottom of my heart, to all of you for continuing to support me, inspire me, and motivate me to keep playing shows and making more music. This is just the beginning, Planet Zuzy is a world very much still undiscovered 👩‍🚀💛

home for a little bit

Okay, I know I’ve been quiet, let me explain. I feel like I have enough to say to make a fucking documentary but I’m gonna keep it short & sweet, for now. 

I finally get to tell you that I’ve started a residency at the brand new @voltairelv in LAS FUCKING VEGAS. 

Voltaire isn’t just a club, nor is it just a residency. It’s a completely new, yet nostalgic take on nightlife. Not only do I get to DJ every weekend along side an incredible team & talent, the one and only @djjellybeanbenitez @kylieminogue , @xtina & @nilerodgers , but I also get to contribute to Voltaire’s Belle De Nuit show, created by @manonsavary & @marczaffuto 

This is a brand new chapter, and I can’t wait to see how it unfolds. In the mean time, a little gift from me to you, my edition of @jorjasmith_ ‘s Little Things drops tomorrow 🪩

“Little Things” is ouuuutt 🥂 Made a little music video, all yours tomorrow
